org.goobi.production.model.bibliography.course

Class IndividualIssue

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.goobi.production.model.bibliography.course.IndividualIssue

  • public class IndividualIssue
extends Object
    The class IndividualIssue represents a stamping of an Issue, that is one distinguishable physically appeared issue (meanwhile the class Issue represents the type of issue).

    The class IndividualIssue is final.

    Author:
    Matthias Ronge <matthias.ronge@zeutschel.de>

    • Method Detail

      • getBreakMark

        public int getBreakMark(Granularity mode)
        Returns an integer which, for a given Granularity, shall indicate for two neighbouring individual issues whether they form the same process (break mark is equal) or to different processes (break mark differs).
        Parameters:
        mode - how the course shall be broken into processes
        Returns:
        an int which differs if two neighbouring individual issues belong to different processes

      • getGenericFields

        public Map<String,String> getGenericFields()
        The function getGenericFields() returns a map with generic fields that can be configured for process title creation in kitodo_projects.xml. It provides the issue information in the following fields:
        #DAY
        two-digit day of month
        #Issue
        issue name
        #MONTH
        two-digit month of year
        #YEAR
        four-digit year

        In addition, the following abbreviated fields are provided:

        #i
        first letter of issue name in lower case
        #I
        first letter of issue name in upper case
        #is
        first two letters of issue name in lower case
        #IS
        first two letters of issue name in upper case
        #iss
        first three letters of issue name in lower case
        #ISS
        first three letters of issue name in upper case
        #issu
        first four letters of issue name in lower case
        #ISSU
        first four letters of issue name in upper case
        #YR
        two-digit year of century
        Returns:
        the generic fields for process title creation
